### Example: Case 1 (Ideal Guide) ###

# Description
This example demonstrates the inversion workflow for a synthetic three-block model using AdaL1TV regularization. In this calculation, the true synthetic model is used as an ideal guide model.

It provides the necessary scripts to reproduce Figures 1 through 4 from the following manuscript:

Utsugi, M., (2026). Adaptive L1-Anisotropic Total Variation Regularization for 3D Magnetic Inversion, Computers & Geosciences (submitted).

# Workflow Overview
The entire workflow is automated via the provided shell script run.sh.

This script performs the AdaL1TV inversion as follows:

../bin/l1tvinv -f input_mag.in -l -2. -g true.quide:1.e-4:1.:1. -c 1. -s settings.par -v

* Input: input_mag.in (pre-included magnetic anomaly dataset).
* Input: true.guide (pre-included true weighted model file used as a guide).

[ Final Output ]
By executing ./run.sh, the final model file is automatically generated as:

model.data

# Visualization
Once the inversion is complete, you can visualize the estimated model and data misfits.

Open and run the provided Jupyter Notebook:

Case1_display_results.ipynb

This notebook generates Figures 1, 2, 3, and 4 shown in the manuscript.
